  "reasoning": "The article reports kinetic parameters (Km and Vmax) for four vanadium‑oxide nanozymes (Vnps‑I, Vnps‑II, Vnps‑III, Vnps‑IV) in two different enzyme‑mimic reactions:\n\n1. **Peroxidase‑like (POD) activity** – substrate H₂O₂, co‑substrate TMB (fixed at 0.2 mM).  \n   - Kinetic assays were performed at 25 °C, pH 7.4 and pH 6.0, with catalyst concentration 0.05 mg mL⁻¹.  \n   - The H₂O₂ concentration was varied from 0.2 mM to 6.0 mM (c_min = 0.2 mM, c_max = 6.0 mM).  \n   - Table 1 provides Km (mM) and Vmax (M s⁻¹) for Vnps‑III and Vnps‑IV (Vnps‑I and Vnps‑II gave no measurable POD activity under the tested conditions).\n\n2. **Catalase‑like (CAT) activity** – substrate H₂O₂, no co‑substrate (c_const = null).  \n   - Kinetic assays were performed at 25 °C, pH 7.4 and pH 6.0, with catalyst concentration 0.05 mg mL⁻¹.  \n   - H₂O₂ concentration was varied from 50 mM to 600 mM (c_min = 50 mM, c_max = 600 mM).  \n   - Table 2 gives Km (mM) and Vmax (mg L⁻¹ min⁻¹) for all four nanozymes (Vnps‑I, Vnps‑II, Vnps‑III, Vnps‑IV) at the indicated pH values.\n\nFor each distinct set of parameters we create a separate experiment object, filling the schema fields with the extracted values:\n\n- **formula**: “V2O5” (the vanadium oxide precursor).  \n- **activity**: “peroxidase” for POD experiments, “catalase” for CAT experiments.  \n- **surface**: “PVP” (the polymer used in synthesis).  \n- **length**: 10 nm (average particle diameter from TEM).  \n- **ccat_value** / **ccat_unit**: 0.05 mg mL⁻¹.  \n- **ph**, **temperature**, **c_const**, **c_const_unit**, **c_min**, **c_max**, **km_value**, **km_unit**, **vmax_value**, **vmax_unit**, **reaction_type** are populated according to the tables and experimental description.  \n- **syngony**, **width**, **depth**, **surface**, **polymer**, **surfactant** are left null when not explicitly reported.\n\nAll extracted experiments are listed below as a valid `NanozymeExtractionOutput` JSON object."
